<br>
I was reading the DragonLance series and loving every minute of it.  In partucular, I identified with the character of Raistlin. He was the sickly weak mage, and twin of Caramon, a strong, handome warrior.<br>
<br>
Raistlin was thin and frail and always sick.  He could barely even eat anything if I remember correctly, just surviving on a herbal tea/soup he brewed.  He was a very bitter young man, power hungry, and jealous of his brother's good-looks and excellent physical health.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I started to notice after the third book or so that I was not eating,  (I would often just drink tea), I was constantly sick, and I was bitter towards the world.  I distincly remember digging out an old black blanket and wearing it around the house all day (Raist was a black robed mage).<br>
<br>
Looking back, all I can say is, I'm a freak!<br>
